author: NSPBWii
text:
Checkpoint 3

This is the third time I try to write this. Last Checkpoint was 3 weeks ago in a boiling volcano. I'm also finally 24 years old. My birthday was 3 days ago. And it was the most disappointing week I've ever had. So many depressing realizations.

First of all, my family doesn't love me for what I am. They love me for what I can be. I can never please them, and they will never listen to me truthfully. I wanted to eat pizza just with my closer family, but they got other plans, and they did everything to have their own way. I tried to show them the things I really cared about, and they did nothing but judge me for it and tell me to stop. And then I realized that I can't be myself with them. I can never please them with what I am. They will always ask "Why don't you have a girlfriend? Why don't you do this or that? Go to Canada. Stop being in the computer so much. Stop playing videogames." Be yourself, but don't be yourself. Be whatever concept of yourself we think you are.

But I was hopeful. The next day I would be with my best friends, my second family. Even my crush was going to be there. This was my chance to finally kiss her and start something good. But everyone cancelled or didn't even responded. It was just my best friend, my crush and me. I bored her. The magic wore off. That crushed me.

Each year, less and less people care about me. I definitely have fans, people that admire me at a surface level. But I can't be honest about myself with no one. They tell me I'm exaggerating, that I'm a crybaby, lazy, dramatic. Over the years, I feel more and more lonely. More and more lost. I can't trust anybody. Not my family, not the people I date, not even my closest friends.

So here I am now, lost in the swamp, in the middle of the mud, watching the starry sky, hopeless. What's the point of staying alive if I can't trust no one? If there's no one to hold me when I fall? What's the point of living if no one will ever care about me? Where's everyone while I lie in this metaphorical swamp?

No one cares. They only care about the surface, and my potential. I will never be good enough. I want to lash out and reject everything I'm supposed to be. But there's no job that can allow me that kind of freedom right now. I have to wait until I get my college degree and my first serious job. But that doesn't feel like a solution, either. I wouldn't be really free. And I don't have the talent to make a living off my passions. I feel so hopeless. Maybe I should let the earth eat me alive, and end this pointless life.

But if that could happen, I would be in this Checkpoint, anyway.

I truthfully don't want my life to end, but I really don't like how it is right now. I've spent years trying to understand what's wrong with me, and why nobody can truly love me. Treating me like the problem. Like I'm not worthy. Now I'm 24 years old, and I can't make mistakes anymore. I lost my best years trying to be what everyone else wanted from me, just to feel loved. And it didn't even worked.

I Don't want to be alone, but I have no choice. I think I will cry beneath the night sky for a while. I will mourn for the life I will never have, and then accept the life I do have. Do the best I can with it. I have no other choice.

This will definitely get lost in between all the other checkpoints, but I want to thank you all anyway. Writing helps me to let go the pain. I feel better now. Thank you. See you in the next Checkpoint. 4 is my favorite number.

Sincerely:
A 24 Year Old Mexican
08/Sep/2020

author: Brenda Kowalewycz
text:
Checkpoint #3

I‚Äôve passed on a couple of checkpoints, not feeling like I‚Äôve needed them so soon after the last... but today... I needed this one...

I‚Äôve been feeling quite depressed in the last few days, my health seems to be improving at a snails pace, if at all. I have no motivation to clean my room, do my dishes or anything. I feel both stuck in the one spot and like I‚Äôm wandering endless halls with no way out...

Which is why I needed this checkpoint. I need a break from the wandering. I thought this checkpoint was scary at first, certainly it is a little darker than the others.. yet I can‚Äôt shake the feeling that it is exactly what I needed right now. Perhaps I wouldn‚Äôt have felt worthy of a brighter checkpoint... whatever the reason, I‚Äôm grateful for the reminder that I‚Äôm still the main character in my story and the main character always has problems to solve and darkness‚Äôs to navigate. This too shall pass.

Game saved: 6:00pm Saturday 11/07/2020

author: Feelinara
text:
This is checkpoint 3 for me. But this one doesn't really feel like a checkpoint - more like I'm moving through an area...I don't know. Everything feels more alive. To fit the vibe, I'm not doing a sad one this time.
I'm feeling pretty good today, which is weird. Actually following the advice my doctor gives makes me feel healthier. Who knew. Anyway, school is over and I finally have time to read all the books I've been wanting to! And places are opening up for indoor dining again. I don't care if I die, all I want is a meal from Perkins while I sit and read for hours in the middle of the night. That's one of the highlights of summer for me, honestly. Also my cat returning to her sunny nap spots...they don't work nearly as well in the winter lol.
